<p>Westside neighborhoods near the lake experience more moderate temperatures due to Lake Erie's thermal mass effect, potentially reducing heating costs but increasing humidity concerns that efficient HVAC systems must address. The Harborcreek area, with its mix of residential types, sees varying solar potential based on lot orientation and tree coverage. Throughout all neighborhoods, homes built before 1980 typically require electrical upgrades to support solar installations, while newer constructions in areas like Fairview generally have infrastructure ready for renewable energy systems.</p>

